  "text": "As secondary outcomes, we compared the final characteristics of 114 patients followed up with 12 months between intervention and UC groups. Patients in the IC arm showed a lower percentage of current smokers (UC, 16% vs. ICS, 3%, P = 0.02), better COPD knowledge and self-management (50% vs. 71%, P = 0.02), lower depression score (Anxiety and Depression Scale, HADS) [CITATION_1] (mean 7 vs. 5, P o 0.01) and fewer symptoms score in the St George's Respiratory Questionnaire (mean 42 vs. 32, P = 0.02) than in the UC arm (Table 3) .",
